---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<style>
body.accessibility-page {
  background: #FAF6F4 !important;
}
</style>

<Layout title="Accessibility | Hoogly" description="Accessibility statement for Hoogly.ai." type="website" bodyClass="accessibility-page">
  <section style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 3rem 1.5rem; background: #FAF6F4; border-radius: 20px;">
    <h1 style="font-size: 2.5rem; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Accessibility Statement for Hoogly</h1>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1.2rem;"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 1st July 2025</p>
    <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      At Hoogly, we are committed to ensuring that our platform is accessible and inclusive for all users, including people with disabilities. We believe that everyone should be able to connect meaningfully and build a sense of belonging â€” and that starts with access.
    </p>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.7rem;">Our Commitment</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1.2rem;">
      We strive to design, build, and test our software in accordance with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1, Level AA. These guidelines help make web content more accessible for people with a wide range of abilities, including those who use assistive technologies.
    </p>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.7rem;">Current Accessibility Features</h2>
    <ul style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding-left: 1.2em;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Mobile and Desktop version of the app</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Keyboard navigation for key user journeys</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Screen reader compatibility for major user flows</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Sufficient colour contrast for readability</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Scalable text for improved legibility</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.7rem;">Ongoing Improvements</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 0.7rem;">We are actively working to improve the accessibility of our platform. As part of our product development process, we:</p>
    <ul style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding-left: 1.2em;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Consider accessibility in all new features</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Conduct periodic internal audits</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 0.5em;">Welcome feedback from users and institutions</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.7rem;">VPAT</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      We are currently preparing a Voluntary Product Accessibility Template (VPAT) to provide more detailed information about our compliance with accessibility standards. We expect to make this available shortly.
    </p>
    <h2 style="font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.7rem;">Feedback</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1.2rem;">
      If you encounter any accessibility barriers while using Hoogly, or if you have suggestions for improvement, please contact us through our support page:
    </p>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
      ðŸ”— <a href="https://hoogly.ai/contact-us/" style="color: #6c63ff; text-decoration: underline;">https://hoogly.ai/contact-us/</a>
    </p>
    <p style="font-size: 1.1rem;">
      We are committed to addressing accessibility issues promptly and continuously improving our user experience for everyone.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout> 